annotationA: ER lumen protein-retaining receptor; Required for the retention of luminal endoplasmic reticulum proteins. Determines the specificity of the luminal ER protein retention system. Also required for normal vesicular traffic through the Golgi (By similarity)
annotationB: Mesencephalic astrocyte-derived neurotrophic factor homolog; Required during the maturation of the embryonic nervous system for maintenance of neuronal and cuticular connectivity. Essential for maintenance of dopaminergic neurons and dopamine levels
